# TASK_PACKET

Task ID
CRUSHR-FORMAT-08

Title
Implement and compare metadata placement strategies for graph-supporting recovery metadata

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Add bounded experimental metadata-placement strategies for graph-supporting recovery metadata and compare their effect on metadata survivability and recovery outcomes.

This packet does NOT change payload identity semantics.
It changes where recovery-supporting metadata is placed so we can measure whether any placement strategy better preserves salvageable truth under corruption.

The three required placement strategies are:

1. fixed_spread
2. hash_spread
3. golden_spread

These strategies apply only to graph-supporting metadata surfaces such as:

- file manifest checkpoints
- path checkpoints
- recovery / bootstrap anchors if present in the current experimental archive path

This packet must preserve the project’s core rules:

- crushr is integrity-first
- crushr-extract remains strict-only
- no speculative reconstruction
- no guessed filenames, offsets, or ordering
- only fully verified metadata and fully verified content may be used

This remains experimental and opt-in.

